functionsDescriptions.absDescription: Returns the absolute value of a number, a number without its sign
functionsDescriptions.andDescription: Checks whether all arguments are TRUE, and returns TRUE if all arguments are true
functionsDescriptions.averageDescription: Returns average (arithmentic mean) of tis arguments
functionsDescriptions.ceilingDescription: Rounds a number up, to the nearest multiple of significance
functionsDescriptions.chooseDescription: Chooses a value from a list of values, based on an index number
functionsDescriptions.concatenateDescription: Joins several text string into one text string
functionsDescriptions.dateDescription: Returns the number that represents the date in Microsoft Excel date-time code
functionsDescriptions.dayDescription: Returns the day of the month, a number from 1 to 31
functionsDescriptions.daysinmonthDescription: Returns number of days in a month/year combination
functionsDescriptions.findDescription: Return the starting position of one text string within another text string. FIND is case-sensitive
functionsDescriptions.floorDescription: Rounds a number down, to the nearest multiple of significance
functionsDescriptions.ifDescription: Checks whether a condition is met, and return one value if true, and another value if false
functionsDescriptions.isEmptyDescription: Checks whether the given input represents an empty value (NaN)
functionsDescriptions.leftDescription: Returns the specified number of characters from the start of a text string
functionsDescriptions.lenDescription: Returns the number of characters in a text string
functionsDescriptions.lookupDescription: Looks for a value in the specified dictionary table using provided keys as another parameters
functionsDescriptions.maxDescription: Returns the largest number in a set of values
functionsDescriptions.midDescription: Returns the characters from the middle of a text string, given a starting position and length
functionsDescriptions.minDescription: Returns the smallest number in a set of values
functionsDescriptions.modDescription: Returns the reminder after a number is divided by a divisor
functionsDescriptions.monthDescription: Returns the month, a number from 1 (January) to 12 (December)
functionsDescriptions.notDescription: Changes FALSE to TRUE, or TRUE to FALSE
functionsDescriptions.orDescription: Checks whether any of the arguments is TRUE, and returns TRUE or FALSE. Returns FALSE if all of the arguments are FALSE
functionsDescriptions.rightDescription: Return the specified number of characters from the end of the text string
functionsDescriptions.roundDescription: Rounds a number to a specified number of digits
functionsDescriptions.signDescription: Returns the sign of a number, 1 if the number is positive, zero if the number is zero, or -1 if the number is negative
functionsDescriptions.sqrtDescription: Returns the square root of a number
functionsDescriptions.todayDescription: Returns the current date in Microsoft Excel date-time code
functionsDescriptions.yearDescription: Returns the year of a date, an integer in the reange 1900-9999
